# Package Manager: Use Yarn

This project uses **yarn** as the package manager. Always use `yarn` commands instead of `npm`.

## Common Commands

```bash
# ❌ WRONG
npm install
npm install <package>
npm run <script>
npm test
npm ci

# ✅ CORRECT
yarn install
yarn add <package>
yarn <script>
yarn test
yarn install --frozen-lockfile
```

## Development Dependencies

```bash
# ❌ WRONG
npm install --save-dev <package>

# ✅ CORRECT
yarn add -D <package>
```

## Key Points

- Use `yarn.lock` (never `package-lock.json`)
- Run `yarn install` after pulling changes
- Use `yarn add` to add new dependencies
- Use `yarn add -D` for dev dependencies
